	<LINE>TARIFF (INLAND).</LINE>
	<LINE>The charge for the transmission of Messages by Telegraph through&lt;jut the</LINE>
	<LINE>United Kingdom is Is. for the first 20 words, and 3d. for each additional five</LINE>
	<LINE>words or part of five words ; the names and addresses of the sender and re-</LINE>
	<LINE>ceiver not being counted.</LINE>
	<LINE>Telegrams may be repeated at the request of the sender, if he desires to</LINE>
	<LINE>adopt this extra security against risk of error, by being signalled back from</LINE>
	<LINE>each office at which they are received to the office from which they are for-</LINE>
	<LINE>warded. The charge for repetition is one half the ordinary tariff : fractions</LINE>
	<LINE>of threeijence being reckoned as twopence.</LINE>
	<LINE>The cost of a reply to a Telegram may be prepaid.</LINE>
	<LINE>Copies of a Telegram, dii-ected to more than one firm or person in the same</LINE>
	<LINE>free delivery, London excepted, will be delivered separately at an additional</LINE>
	<LINE>charge of threepence per copy.</LINE>
	<LINE>Numbers expressed in figures are counted as so man j'^ words according to</LINE>
	<LINE>the number of figures employed. Fractions are counted in a similar manner,</LINE>
	<LINE>with the exception that one word is added for the bar bstween numerator</LINE>
	<LINE>and denominator, thus i counts as three words.</LINE>
